@page "/docs/installation"

<PageTitle>Installation - GuideFlow Docs</PageTitle>

<div class="docs-content">
    <h1>Installation</h1>
    <p class="docs-lead">Install the NuGet package, register the service in <code>Program.cs</code>, and add the CSS/JS references. Works with both Blazor Server and Blazor WebAssembly - no JavaScript dependencies required.</p>

    <h2 id="nuget">
        Install via NuGet
        <a class="docs-anchor" href="#nuget">#</a>
    </h2>

    <p>Run the following command in your project directory:</p>

    <CodeBlock Language="bash" Code="dotnet add package GuideFlow" />

    <p>Or install via the NuGet Package Manager:</p>

    <CodeBlock Language="powershell" Code="Install-Package GuideFlow" />

    <h2 id="register-service">
        Register the Service
        <a class="docs-anchor" href="#register-service">#</a>
    </h2>

    <p>In your <code>Program.cs</code>, add the GuideFlow service:</p>

    <CodeBlock Language="csharp" Code="@(@"using GuideFlow.Services;

var builder = WebAssemblyHostBuilder.CreateDefault(args);
// ... other registrations

builder.Services.AddGuideFlow();

await builder.Build().RunAsync();")" />

    <div class="docs-note docs-note--info">
        <strong>💡 Server-Side Blazor</strong>
        For Blazor Server projects, use <code>builder.Services.AddGuideFlow()</code> in your <code>Program.cs</code> the same way.
        GuideFlow supports both WebAssembly and Server hosting models.
    </div>

    <h2 id="add-css">
        Add the CSS
        <a class="docs-anchor" href="#add-css">#</a>
    </h2>

    <p>Reference the GuideFlow stylesheet in your <code>index.html</code> (WebAssembly) or <code>_Host.cshtml</code> (Server):</p>

    <CodeBlock Language="html" Code="@(@"<link href=""_content/GuideFlow/guideflow.css"" rel=""stylesheet"" />")" />

    <h2 id="import-namespaces">
        Import Namespaces
        <a class="docs-anchor" href="#import-namespaces">#</a>
    </h2>

    <p>Add these namespaces to your <code>_Imports.razor</code>:</p>

    <CodeBlock Language="razor" Code="@(@"@using GuideFlow.Components
@using GuideFlow.Enums
@using GuideFlow.Models
@using GuideFlow.Services")" />

    <h2 id="verify">
        Verify Installation
        <a class="docs-anchor" href="#verify">#</a>
    </h2>

    <p>Create a simple tour to verify everything works:</p>

    <CodeBlock Language="razor" Code="@(@"@page ""/test""

<button id=""test-target"" @onclick=""StartTour"">Start Tour</button>

<GuideFlowTour @ref=""tour"" TourOptions=""options"">
    <GuideFlowStep Selector=""#test-target"" Title=""It works!"" Order=""0"">
        <p>GuideFlow is installed correctly.</p>
    </GuideFlowStep>
</GuideFlowTour>

@code {
    private GuideFlowTour? tour;
    private TourOptions options = new() { Overlay = true };

    private async Task StartTour()
    {
        if (tour != null) await tour.DriveAsync();
    }
}")" />

    <div class="docs-note docs-note--tip">
        <strong>✅ Next Step</strong>
        Head to <a href="docs/quick-start">Quick Start</a> to build a complete multi-step tour.
    </div>
</div>
